# First occurrence: -A (prepend, AUDIT_FILTER_PREPEND = 0x10).
# After insertion the kernel CLEARS the prepend bit in the stored entry:
#   kernel/auditfilter.c:1003  entry->rule.flags &= ~AUDIT_FILTER_PREPEND
# So the already-loaded entry has flags == 0.
-A always,exit -S execve -F auid>=1000 -k exec
